full_description:
With a new visual identity that reflects the energy, diversity and spirit of togetherness that define the event, the Oeiras Festivities are reinventing themselves without losing their essence.
Renowned for its attractive programme and its ability to bring together different generations, the Oeiras Festivities have established themselves, over the years, as one of the most significant events on the municipality’s cultural calendar, reflecting its identity, diversity and social dynamics.
More than just a series of festive events, this occasion serves as a meeting place for people, generations, artistic expressions and cultural experiences, establishing itself as a collective celebration open to all, promising unique moments to enjoy with family or friends. In addition to music, the venue offers a complete experience, with dining areas, street food, crafts, entertainment and a lounge area where you can sample the iconic Villa Oeiras fortified wine.
More than just a party, it is a collective, inclusive and vibrant celebration that brings together people, experiences and cultures through a diverse cultural and sporting programme, spread across various locations in the municipality.
• Major concerts and plenty of live music;
• Food and drink areas with options to suit all tastes;
• Street food;
• Handicrafts;
• Lounge area for relaxing and socialising;
• Entertainment for children, young people and adults;
• Daily entertainment and surprises throughout the programme.
🕑
Opening hours
Oeiras Municipal Garden (Oeiras Train Station)
Weekdays: Food and drink, crafts and entertainment, from 5 pm to midnight
Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays: Food and drink from 12 noon to midnight, crafts and entertainment from 3 pm to midnight
